  "content": "<p>2\ufe0f\u20e37\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 27th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>You might have heard of systemd-confext before. It&#39;s just like systemd-sysext, but applies its magic to /etc/ rather than /usr/. In case you never heard of systemd-sysext either: it&#39;s a mechanism for merging a number of disk images (DDIs specifically) on top of /usr/ via overlayfs so that /usr/ becomes a stack of (immutable) images, that appears as one file system tree.</p>",
